According to Juuri, who came to have fun in the Old Town on Saturday night, the fear of the coronavirus has driven partygoers away. While they used to meet up with friends there, now they would rather do it at home, and only groups of young people continue to hang out near the museum as before.
Please, please, nothing is happening.
It's a shame, a shame that the Old Town is dying, slowly dying.
